Howdy I'm Wednesday. I was wandering outside by myself where I was found by some nice folks and brought to safety. Yeah, you're assuming it was a Wednesday, huh? Nope, they named me after Wednesday from the Addams Family -- ha, ha, fooled ya! Anyhoo, I'm a friendly, active girl always joking around like that, come meet me soon!







To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Mario was named after Mario Andretti as from an early age, he and his fellow racer-named siblings (Danika and Pippa) love to jet around at top speed.  He is a sweet and energetic love bug who is full of kisses and is brimming with confidence.

Hello, I'm Eleanor Rigby, a beautiful New Zealand White girl released from a medical testing facility. Up til now my life was spent in a laboratory but I'm eager to see what the big wide world has to offer and hope to find a forever home where I'll be cherished member of the family. 



I arrived with a group of 12 laboratory bunnies, collectively #TheBeatlesBunnies and named after favorite songs. Feel free to sing my song when we meet!To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable
Very friendly and perky kitty! She loves to cuddle and be pet and also to play! Ziggy was named after her ziggy zag shaped tail tip.
This little one is getting ready for the day he will be ready for adoption. www.luckypawshawaii.org/adopt

Hello new friends! Are you looking for a super sweet dog to love forever? I think you should choose me! I would make the greatest companion for a adventure, but I would also be happy right at home with you! I am great with dogs, and people too! I have lots of energy and love to give, so it would benefit me greatly to have lots of exercise. Who doesn't love a good walk with their best friend though? Take me home!

Izzy is FIV/ FELV negative and parasite-free.  She is a sweet girl who is very playful and independent,  She loves playing with toys and chasing small balls.   Izzy was rescued as a small kitten and found tangled up in vines. Izzy is a little over 3 month old and is playful, independent and a loving cat that also has a feisty side.  She was rescued, she was tangled up in weeds. A good samaritan was able to get her out of it.  She does well with other cats with a slow introduction, but she don't not mind getting all the attention to herself. She loves being pet and playing with fuzzy ball. She would do best in a household without any children.

Goose is about 5 month old as of 8/31/21. He can be a little skittish at first, but once he opens up, he is playful, energetic and cuddly. 

He is vaccinated, neutered, microchipped, Fiv/Felv negative, dewormed, littler trained and flea bathed.

Greetings, I'm Pearl and I'm a recent SaveABunny arrival but already a favorite of some of the volunteers (shh, don't tell the other bunnies) for how my ears perk up when they talk to me nicely -- I do love a good compliment!



To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Hi, I'm Loki. I was about to be dumped in a park in San Francisco when a Good Samaritan saw what was happening and intervened. My rescuer talked to the person dumping me and persuaded them to hand me over instead of abandoning me. From there I made my way to SaveABunny.



It was clear I was neglected as I was very skinny and had an old injury -- what looks like a broken leg that was never attended to so it healed a bit crooked, but it doesn't bother me so the vet says just to monitor. I can't tell you how happy I am to be safe and cared for -- and I'm a girl ready to let bygones be bygones and look forward to finding a forever home.To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Hello, I'm Good Day Sunshine, a beautiful New Zealand White girl released from a medical testing facility. Up til now my life was spent in a laboratory but I'm eager to see what the big wide world has to offer and hope to find a forever home where I'll be cherished member of the family. 



I arrived with a group of 12 laboratory bunnies, collectively #TheBeatlesBunnies and named after favorite songs. Feel free to sing my song when we meet!To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

This is one Lab who you can still teach new tricks! I came to Kauai Humane Society as a stray, so the staff isn't sure what my home life was like before I came here. However, they have learned that I LOVE TO LEARN - and treats motivate me to learn all sorts of tricks! I sit and give good eye contact and have learned to walk better on leash all through treats and calm, consistent training.

That's what I would like in my new home - calm, consistent training (and some treats). :-)

I can be initially slow to warm up to people and prone to escape if not handled securely; hence why that consistent training and treats is so important. ;-) And within a day or so, I will warm up and learn my routine so fast!

I have met some dogs I was a little unsure about, and other easy-going, very social puppies that I have done great with. The key to my heart, and to being my best-matched home, is understanding I might start out needing more patience and initial routine than your average pet. Watching me learn and grow is so rewarding!

Rudy is a very sweet boy! He may seem angry when you greet him at his kennel but once you get in his kennel with him and love on him or play with him in the yard he is a total lap dog! Rudy was surrendered to us because their owners are moving to the mainland and couldn't take him with them. Ask us about our boy Rudy! Take him home today!

Hello, I'm Quimby and I'm a handsome young boy. Don't you like the butterfly I carry around on my nose? We like playing together, dancing and flying!To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Hola, mi nombre es Cuervo, and I'm named after a tequila -- I'm a teetotaler who sticks strictly to water, but I like my name anyways cuz it's fun to say out loud. My favorite thing to do is stand up! 



To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

This little nugget was found on the road of Kaneohe marine corps base by some visitors to the island. They took good care of him, took him on adventures, and called Lucky Paws to help before they depart Oahu. This kitty is a top gem. Very social already and likes dogs and cats alike thus far. has lots of energy.

Hello I'm Lovebug, a friendly girl who always wants to help with whatever you're doing and be involved with everything that's going on. A real busybody!To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable
To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

This little girl was found with sibling Bullseye. Both had terrible ringworm which is being treated. The ringworm makes for a terrible picture but she will be a beautiful white and orange kitty when healed.

Hi I'm Parchment, if you need me for anything just call and I'll hop right on over! 



I was just a couple weeks old when I came here with my mom Cotton Candy and my sibs, part of a confiscation of 29 bunnies by authorities due to extreme neglect. Mom was so brave protecting all of us and we grew up healthy and thriving and now I'm ready to experience everything life has to offer.



To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

petData.description: Marv is a playful boy who loves all the pets in the world! Marv was a rescue we picked up, along with his brother Harry,  around the Dole Plantation. They are both so loving and can be clingy, but who doesn't love that?! Harry and Marv have been strays their whole life so it will take time to adjust to a home setting. They have settled in very nicely with us, they are pleasant on the leash and very friendly. Ask us more about the dynamic duo and adopt Marv today or both of the brothers!

Hello, I'm Oslo, I'm an older Californian boy and this is Maris (white lop), my hot young girlfriend. We were adopted a while ago then returned when our human could not take care of us any more, but look forward to creating a new future together.



To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Hi there, I'm Bam Bam and I'm a teeny tiny little guy -- I'm may struggle to tip the scales at 2 lbs, but I'm packed with personality and have big, big plans to rule the world!

Hi I'm a young, cute lion head boy. I don't roar though, I'd rather play then settle down for a nice cuddle and nap and maybe a nice head rub.To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

This was part of a litter who was rescued from Sonny's Auto at Sand Island. Mama was missing and babies were in a bad place. Flashy is FAST! She loves to play and dart around the cage. She enjoys wrestling the siblings, eating slurry, and taking long naps. Very cuddly and loves to sleep near your head. She is just a little kitty but shes a BIG treasure! Shes VERY cottonball-like and is calico. Mostly Grey, legs white, orange stripe on face. Very cool!

Elvis is a fun loving goofy boy! He loves to play in the yard with lots of toys and can keep himself entertained. He has a lot of energy and needs a strong handler, sometimes he doesn't know how big he actually is! Adopt Elvis today you will never be bored with him!

Am still a little shy and getting to know everyone but soon my dutchie 'tude will start to shine through -- and you should see me binky and dance when I'm out to play!To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Hi I'm Henry Huggins and I'm a young boy who's just an all-around nice guy just like the character I'm named after from the ""Beezus and Ramona"" books by children's author Beverly Cleary.To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Justin is a super sweet and SUPER soft male rex rabbit ready and waiting for a new home! He would make a great companion for anyone ready to take on life with a house rabbit. Justin and Lance are brothers and wouldn't mind going home together. 



All Humane Society of Sonoma County rabbits are companion house rabbits. They live indoors only and cage free- living in a pen or free-roam in the home. This lets them live much longer, happier lives! Indoor rabbits can live 12+ years and require a lot of time and commitment. In return they offer years of love and companionship! Primary Color: White Secondary Color: Black Weight: 2.2kg Age: 1yrs 1mths 2wks Animal has been Neutered

Zelda is a very sweet girl! She loves to play with her toys and would thrive as the only dog in the house hold. Zelda has been in foster for sometime now so we are not sure how she is with other kids, since the foster does not have any kids. Zelda does like to rough house play so she would benefit from a strong handler. Ask us more about Zelda today and take her home!

Hi I'm Paperback, a young girl who jumps out of bed in the morning to eagerly greet the day -- I'm friendly and interactive, too! 



To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable
To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Are you looking for an outdoor adventurer? Look no further! I would be the greatest friend for a nice hike, or even a day playing on the beach. I am a great companion for other dogs, and people too! If you take me home, I will try to be the goodest boy ever! I can't wait to find my forever family!

Hallo, I'm Halo, a young boy still growing into my ears. They flap all over the place, creating quite a nice cooling breeze! 



Here's me when I was a bit younger. 







To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Ka'eo is living his best life in his foster home! His very sweet fosters are not able to adopt him because they will be moving off the island soon. We would love for him to find his forever home where he can retire so he doesn't have to come back to the shelter! He is very sweet, we picked him up a few months back at Hawaiian Humane Society all skin and bones. We fed him and gave him all the love and more! He looks so good now and relaxing in his foster home. If you are interested in senior dogs and giving them their forever home, contact us today! Mahalo.

Aloha! My name is Sir Wallace and I am the sweetest boy around. When I arrived at the shelter, I was pretty sick and in bad shape, but the staff saved me and got me into a foster home. I am now healthy, flourishing, and ready for my forever home. I love playing with my older dog siblings and especially love my cat sibling. Foster reports that Sir Wallace is super smart, picked up walking on a leash, and house training quickly. He is good with kids, cats, and other dogs. Despite his unlucky beginnings, he is a trusting, loving, and outgoing pup now. Give this perfect pup a home!

Hello there I'm Blush, and I'm a very pretty girl with charm to spare. But because my ears are kind of fancy I need my human guardian to pay close attention and help me clean them frequently so they don't become gunked up and infected.

To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable

Oh hi there, I'm Tinsel (silver) and this is Roxy (white). I'm a friendly and people-loving middle-aged girl adopted from SaveABunny a while back. Roxy became my BFF gal pal a couple years ago. We're back here because our guardians moved out of the country and were not able to take us with them. We're children friendly and hope to find a home soon!To see all the available rabbits at SaveABunny, please visit http://www.saveabunny.org/rabbits/allavailable
